{{efn
| name = gun nomenclature
| In Imperial German Navy gun nomenclature, "SK" (''Schnelladekanone'') denotes that the gun is quick firing, while the L/45 denotes the length of the gun. In this case, the L/45 gun is 45 [[Caliber (artillery)|caliber]], meaning that the gun barrel is 45 times as long as it is in diameter.
}}

